title: ICE: assoc-const-ty-mismatch.rs  -Zsave-analysis: 'not yet implemented', compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/at.rs

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code code reduced from `./src/test/ui/associated-consts/assoc-const-ty-mismatch.rs` ```Rust #![feature(associated_const_equality)] #![allow(unused)] pub trait Foo { const N: usize; } pub struct Bar; impl Foo for Bar { const N: usize = 3; } fn foo>() {} //~^ ERROR mismatch in fn main() { foo::(); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.60.0-nightly (1ea485171 2022-02-01) binary: rustc commit-hash: 1ea4851715893ee3f365a8ef09d47165e9a7864f commit-date: 2022-02-01 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.60.0-nightly LLVM version: 13.0.0 (master toolchain) ``` ### Error output `rustc ./src/test/ui/associated-consts/assoc-const-ty-mismatch.rs -Zsave-analysis` ``` error: mismatch in bind of associated constant, got type --> ./src/test/ui/associated-consts/assoc-const-ty-mismatch.rs:15:15 | 15 | fn foo>() {} | ^^^^^^^ | note: associated constant defined here does not match type --> ./src/test/ui/associated-consts/assoc-const-ty-mismatch.rs:5:3 | 5 | const N: usize; | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ thread 'rustc' panicked at 'not yet implemented', compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/at.rs:304:23 note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc 1.60.0-nightly (1ea485171 2022-02-01) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu note: compiler flags: -Z save-analysis query stack during panic: #0 [evaluate_obligation] evaluating trait selection obligation `::N == usize` #1 [typeck] type-checking `main` end of query stack error: aborting due to previous error ```
